Johannesburg IOL apologises for a story we carried earlier on Wednesday suggesting that Judge Mabel&nbsp;Jansen could potentially be criminally prosecuted retroactively for&nbsp; controversial comments she made last year.&nbsp; Jansen cannot be criminally charged as the new proposed Hate Crimes Bill cannot be retrospective. Last year writer Gillian Schutte brought a misconduct complaint to the Judicial Conduct Committee after a private conversation she had with Judge Jansen on Facebook, where the latter stated that rape and murder were part of black people s culture which made her feel like vomiting . The judge has been placed on special leave while the JCC continues to&nbsp; deliberate whether Jansen has a case to answer to. The Star